cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS

This paper deals with shape analysis, which is a topic in program analysis and verification. The use of abstract interpretation and first-order logic suggests that it belongs to the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO) sub-categories. The focus on heap abstractions and dynamically allocated storage suggests that it may also belong to the software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of sets and structures suggests that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
